                <head>Mass Meeting in Alexandria</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Stuart</ln>
                        <fn>A. H. H.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Baldwin</ln>
                        <fn>Jno. B.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Col.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Resolutions produced at a mass meeting held in Alexandria last Tuesday
                    endorsing the Philadelphia National Convention and the "noble and patriotic
                    course of President Johnson." Includes excerpts of letters by A. H. H. Stuart
                    and Jno. Baldwin, both of Augusta, who were invited to attend.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>04</column>
                <head>The Soldiers' Convention</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The platform and resolutions produced at the Soldiers' Convention in
                    Cleveland. The convention endorsed the policy of President Johnson and the
                    Philadelphia National Convention.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
